				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
							<p>Late Mrs. Sumati Phadnis was a retired nurse. She trained at a nursing college in the 40s at a time when very few women were doing nursing. She was a nurse par excellence and provided excellent support to the doctors and caring and compassionate professional care to the patients. She worked tirelessly as a nurse for a span of four decades before she retired. She continued to guide new nurses at Oyster and Pearl Hospital, Pune.</p>						</div>
